This may seem dumb to YOU, but it's MY reality.

I can't bare this pain any longer,
When I look in the mirror I break down and cry,
I'll pretend I don't care what I look like,
But in reality, I do,
I walk around each day wanting to hide my face,
My shame, why must I feel so unbeautiful?
Why must I want so badly to  look like someone else?

Acne, it's more serious then you think,
It consumes my life.

You may not know how bad my acne really is because I cover it up with makeup most of the time. But one of these days if you haven't already you'll see it.

I want to raise acne awareness (I know it I'm making it sound like a disease...but in a way it kind of is) If you know someone (besides me) that has acne tell them they're beautiful! Look past it and see their beauty within, because it's UNBELIEVABLLY hard to feel beautiful when your face is has red as a stop sign.

Dos and Don'ts

Do- Complement them on their other features. (eyes, smile, etc.)

Don't- Say: "Oh, I have acne too!" unless you REALLY do because that will just make them feel so much worse.

Don't- Ask "Are you doing anything for your acne?" This always upsets me because I'm doing EVERYTHING.

So remember...make a friend with acne today!! haha

I dedicate this blog to Alexis: "It's hard to face the problem when the problem is your face!" Proavtiv didn't work for meeeee.

I love you girl! You're beautiful in everyway!!

Please know I'm not fishing for compliments...
I'm just being honest.

It's mainly for other people...just to let them know I understand.

-Amanda

I've been thinking a lot about what I want to do with my life, & I'm really not quite sure anymore.
It used to be ALL I wanted to do was be a musician,
but how many musicians make it to the big time...think about...not many that's forsure.
I would still love it, but it's really not piratical.


So then I was thinking about psychology of some kind.
I foud neuropsychology really interesting!
So I really wnat to take a course at BCC next year.

Butttt...I also LOVE, LOVE, LOVE! shows like CSI and all those crime sense type of shows.
They're just so much fun to figure out! & I'm not to bad at it either.
So that's also something I'm interested in.

I really have no idea what I want to do.
But I still have time,
so it's all good in the hood. Lol

Sadly, I cannot go with my first chose...
BEACH BUM.

I could live in a shack on the beach and play my guitar with the case open haha.
That would be the life. No worrys.

--Amanda

I wish my life was TV show. She always gets the guy,
She always gets back at her enemies, She always goes on an insane adventure,
& all the problems are worked out by the end of the show or by the time the commercial ends.

Why is that not reality?
Why can't a commercial make everything better?


I need a commercial already!

So yeah, that's why "Life as a tv show" is my name. For that reaosn & because nothing else would work lol.
--Amanda
